Nice work, thanks!
Was this rename discussed somewhere? It probably deserves to have deprecated aliases for the old names.

The general rename issue from algebra to element is discussed at [here](https://leanprover.zulipchat.com/#narrow/stream/116395-maths/topic/.60IsSeparable.60.20and.20.60Algebra.2EIsSeparable.60). But there is no specific discussion for this theorem.
And yes, I believe creating deprecated aliases for the old names is a good idea. Do you think we should do deprecated aliases for all renamed theorems? And for the previous PR #14232  ?
I've checked all theorems changes in this PR. Only `IsSeparable.of_isScalarTower` and `AlgEquiv.isSeparable` are possible to have a deprecated alias. Other theorem's old names are occupied.

```suggestion
theorem isSeparable_algebraMap (x : F) : IsSeparable F (algebraMap F K x) :=
```

```suggestion
protected instance (priority := 100) Algebra.IsSeparable.of_finite : Algebra.IsSeparable F K :=
```
You already have those in scope I think.
You have this line a lot of times. Is it possible to declare `F`, `K`... only once?
I have reorganized the structure of theorems by their conditions so that the variables are declared only once.

```suggestion
  IsSeparable.of_algHom e.symm ((e₂.symm_apply_apply x).symm ▸ this)

lemma Algebra.IsSeparable.of_equiv_equiv {A₁ B₁ A₂ B₂ : Type*} [Field A₁] [Field B₁]
```

```suggestion
theorem AlgEquiv.Algebra.isSeparable [Algebra.IsSeparable F K] : Algebra.IsSeparable F E :=
```

```suggestion
  ⟨fun _ ↦ AlgEquiv.Algebra.isSeparable e, fun _ ↦ AlgEquiv.Algrebra.isSeparable e.symm⟩
```
Fixed. Thanks!
Why is this protected?
`protected instance (priority := 100) Algebra.IsSeparable.of_finite` is protected to avoid confusion with the elementwise lemma theorem `IsSeparable.of_finite` once you open Algebra.

```suggestion
/-- If `E / L / F` is a scalar tower and `x : E` is separable over `F`, then it's also separable
```
Why a new `section` here? Why don't you need a section name? Perhaps `ScalarTower`?
Here in this part of the file, every single theorem has a different list of variables (E F being Ring or Field, ...). I open new sections to control these variables.
Here in this part of the file, every single theorem has a different list of variables (E F being Ring or Field, ...). I open new sections to control these variables.
I've added names for these sections. Thanks!

```suggestion
/-- If `E / K / F` is a scalar tower and `algebraMap K E x` is separable over `F`, then `x` is
``
Perhaps `section AlgHom` or something like this?
Thank you! Added.
I would do this proof in tactic mode, but that's personal taste.
The last author did it in term mode, so I inherited the term mode proof and made a minimal change.

```suggestion
  let _ : Algebra E E' := RingHom.toAlgebra f.toRingHom
```
Is it possible to `open` Algebra everywhere and avoid having `Algebra.` at all places?

I've tried but this does not work well, since based on current naming conventions, either one needs `Algebra.` or one needs `_root_.`. There are too many lemmas getting the same name after `open Algebra`.

```suggestion
  have := IsSeparable.tower_top A₂ h
```

```suggestion
    have : Algebra.IsSeparable F i.fieldRange :=
```

```suggestion
  fun _ ↦ IsSeparable.tower_top E
```

```suggestion
  ⟨isSeparable_algebraMap⟩
```

```suggestion
  ⟨fun _ => _root_.IsSeparable.of_finite _ _⟩
```
Fixed to `⟨_root_.IsSeparable.of_finite _⟩`
